 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Senior Software Developer, Behavior Planning - Autonomous Vehicles NVIDIA 237 reviews Santa Clara, CA NVIDIA 237 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Want to join a fun, creative company that is on the cutting edge of amazing technologies? NVIDIA is developing groundbreaking solutions in some of the worldâ€™s most exciting technology areas including Virtual Reality, Artificial Intelligence, Deep Learning and Autonomous Vehicles.
 We are looking for software engineers to join our Behavior Planning team to redefine the way we drive. As part of this team you will build our motion and path planning algorithms for various design domains, which spans challenges from achieving a comfortable driving experience, occlusion handling, driver-in-the-loop situations, all the way to the long tail of traffic rules that need to be handled fully autonomously. You will have the opportunity to deploy your algorithms and truly have the first-hand experience of your work driving the cars of the future.
 What you will be doing:
 Develop algorithms for motion and behavior planning on highways and urban roads
 Integrate the algorithms into our software stack and mature them to production quality
 Designing the overall software architecture for a particular feature or component
 Validate and test various scenarios in simulation and on the road
 Solve problems of how to combine data driven and classical solutions to create a robust pipeline
 Design a system that works in multiple different settings, e.g. perception sensors, map availability, environmental conditions
 Collaborate with a diverse group of engineers of other domains including perception, mapping, vehicle control and user experience
 What we need to see:
 BS or higher in an engineering technical field (Mechanical, Electrical, Computer Science, Physics, etc.) or equivalent work experience
 3+ years of experience in software development
 Excellent knowledge of C/C++ and a scripting language such as Python
 Comfortable developing in Linux or another Unix based system
 Ability to think analytically and solve technical problems in a compute constrained system
 Ability to multitask and prioritize
 Excellent communication skills
 Ways to stand out from the crowd:
 PhD in a relevant field or related research experience is helpful
 Previous experience working on autonomous vehicles
 Expert level understanding of planning algorithms
 Experience working with a full stack
 Knowledge of CUDA is a plus
 With highly competitive salaries and a comprehensive benefits package, NVIDIA is widely considered to be one of the technology industry's most desirable employers. We have some of the most forward-thinking and hardworking people in the world working with us and our product lines are growing fast in some of the hottest fields such as virtual reality, deep learning, artificial intelligence, graphics virtualization, photo realistic rendering and more.
